org.accada.reader.rprm.core.msg.notification
Class AckNack

java.lang.Object
  org.accada.reader.rprm.core.msg.notification.Document
      org.accada.reader.rprm.core.msg.notification.AckNack

public class AckNack
extends Document

This element defines a reader protocol notification [reply] ACK/NACK. It is used when ACK/NACK is enabled for a notification channel and underlying transport doesn't support ACK.

Java class for ackNack element declaration.

The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

 <element name="ackNack">
   <complexType>
     <complexContent>
       <extension base="{urn:epcglobal:xsd:1}Document">
         <sequence>
           <element name="id" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string"/>
           <element name="reader" type="{urn:epcglobal:rp:xsd:1}ReaderType" minOccurs="0"/>
           <element name="notifyChannelName" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
           <element name="isAck" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}boolean"/>
         </sequence>
       </extension>
     </complexContent>
   </complexType>
 </element>
